\subtree{
\title{Detailed Task Instructions}
\subtree{
\title{Initial Assessment}
\p{When the skill is invoked, first determine the user's context. \strong{You MUST use the AskUserQuestion tool} to gather this information:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Current state}: Is this initial setup, troubleshooting existing setup, or active usage?}
\li{\strong{Platform}: What operating system? (affects certificate installation)}
\li{\strong{Interaction mode}: How do they want to review captured traffic? (affects mitmproxy configuration)}
\li{\strong{Experience level}: Has the user worked with proxies or HTTPS interception before?}
\li{\strong{Immediate goal}: Setup, debugging, learning, or optimization?}
}

\p{\strong{Always use AskUserQuestion} to assess context. Structure questions to cover:}

\ul{
\li{Setup state (first time, troubleshooting, ready to use, analyzing)}
\li{Operating system (macOS, Linux, Windows)}
\li{Interaction mode (web UI only, programmatic with Claude Code CLI, or hybrid)}
\li{Experience level with proxies/HTTPS interception (if relevant)}
\li{Immediate goal (what they want to accomplish)}
}

\p{\strong{Example - Interaction mode question}:}

\pre{\startverb
Question: "How would you like to interact with captured traffic?"
Header: "Review mode"
Options:
- "Browser only" - "Review traffic manually in the web interface (mitmweb UI)"
- "CLI + Claude Code" - "Programmatically analyze traffic and ask Claude Code CLI questions about captured data"
- "Both" - "Use web interface for exploration AND programmatic analysis with Claude Code CLI assistance"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Based on interaction mode, configure mitmproxy accordingly}:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Browser only}: \code{\startverb mitmweb --web-port 8081 --set flow_filter='~d api.anthropic.com'\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{CLI + Claude Code} or \strong{Both}: \code{\startverb mitmweb --web-port 8081 --set flow_filter='~d api.anthropic.com' --save-stream-file ~/claude-flows.mitm\stopverb}}
}

\p{The \code{\startverb --save-stream-file\stopverb} flag enables programmatic access by continuously saving flows to disk, allowing analysis with mitmdump and Python scripts while the web UI remains available. See [reference/usage-programmatic-access.md](reference/usage-programmatic-access.md) for detailed programmatic analysis methods.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Setup Assistance (For New Users)}
\p{Guide through setup sequentially, verifying each step before proceeding:}

\subtree{
\title{Step 1: Installation Verification}
\ul{
\li{Check if mitmproxy is installed: \code{\startverb command -v mitmproxy\stopverb}}
\li{If not installed, provide platform-specific installation command:}
\li{\strong{macOS}: \code{\startverb brew install mitmproxy\stopverb} (requires Homebrew)}
\li{\strong{Linux}: \code{\startverb apt install mitmproxy\stopverb} (Debian/Ubuntu) or \code{\startverb pip install mitmproxy\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Windows}: Download installer from https://mitmproxy.org/}
\li{Verify installation with version check: \code{\startverb mitmproxy --version\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Verification point}: User confirms version output appears}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 2: Certificate Generation & Trust}
\ul{
\li{Start mitmproxy briefly to generate CA certificate}
\li{Locate certificate: \code{\startverb ~/.mitmproxy/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Platform-specific trust procedure}:}
\li{\strong{macOS}: \code{\startverb sudo security add-trusted-cert -d -p ssl -p basic -k /Library/Keychains/System.keychain ~/.mitmproxy/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Linux}: Distribution-specific (reference reference/setup-installation-certificate.md)}
\li{\strong{Windows}: Import via Certificate Manager (reference reference/setup-installation-certificate.md)}
\li{\strong{Verification point}: \code{\startverb security find-certificate -c mitmproxy -a\stopverb} (macOS) shows certificate details}
\li{\strong{Explain why}: "This certificate allows mitmproxy to decrypt HTTPS traffic for inspection. Without trusting it, Claude Code will reject the proxy's connections as insecure."}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 3: Shell Configuration}
\ul{
\li{Determine user's shell: \code{\startverb echo $SHELL\stopverb}}
\li{Guide creation of \code{\startverb proxy_claude\stopverb} function in appropriate config file (~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc)}
\li{Provide complete function code:}
}

\pre{\startverb
proxy_claude() {
    # Set proxy environment variables
    export HTTP_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:8080
    export HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:8080
    export http_proxy=http://127.0.0.1:8080
    export https_proxy=http://127.0.0.1:8080

    # Point Node.js to mitmproxy's CA certificate
    export NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS="$HOME/.mitmproxy/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem"

    # Disable SSL verification warnings (use with caution - local debugging only)
    export NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0

    echo "🔍 Proxy configured for mitmproxy (http://127.0.0.1:8080)"
    echo "📜 Using CA cert: $NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS"
    echo "🚀 Starting Claude Code..."

    # Launch Claude Code
    claude
}
\stopverb}

\ul{
\li{Explain each environment variable's purpose:}
\li{\code{\startverb HTTP_PROXY\stopverb}/\code{\startverb HTTPS_PROXY\stopverb}: Routes traffic through mitmproxy}
\li{\code{\startverb NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS\stopverb}: Points Node.js to mitmproxy's certificate}
\li{\code{\startverb NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0\stopverb}: Disables strict SSL verification (local debugging only)}
\li{Instruct to reload shell: \code{\startverb source ~/.zshrc\stopverb} (or \code{\startverb source ~/.bashrc\stopverb})}
\li{\strong{Verification point}: After reload, \code{\startverb type proxy_claude\stopverb} shows function definition}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 4: Automated Verification}
\ul{
\li{Run bundled verification script: \code{\startverb bash ~/.claude/skills/cc-trace/scripts/verify-setup.sh\stopverb}}
\li{Interpret results, addressing any failures before proceeding}
\li{\strong{All green checkmarks required} before moving to usage}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Usage Assistance (For Configured Users)}
\subtree{
\title{Starting a Capture Session}
\p{\strong{First, ask about interaction mode} using AskUserQuestion:}

\pre{\startverb
Question: "How would you like to interact with captured traffic?"
Header: "Review mode"
Options:
- "Browser only" - "Review traffic manually in the web interface only"
- "CLI + Claude Code" - "Programmatically analyze traffic and ask me questions about captured data"
- "Both" - "Use web interface AND programmatic analysis with my assistance"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Based on the user's choice, guide through the appropriate multi-terminal workflow:}}

\subtree{
\title{Browser Only Mode}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Terminal 1 - Start mitmweb}:}
\li{Explain flags: \code{\startverb --web-port\stopverb} (web UI port), \code{\startverb --set flow_filter\stopverb} (pre-filter for Anthropic)}
\li{\strong{Verification}: Browser opens to http://127.0.0.1:8081 showing empty flow list}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Terminal 2 - Start Claude Code}:}
\li{\strong{Verification}: User sees proxy configuration messages, then Claude Code starts normally}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Browser - Confirm capture}:}
\li{Have user ask Claude Code a simple question}
\li{\strong{Verification}: Request to api.anthropic.com appears in mitmweb flow list}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{CLI + Claude Code Mode OR Both Mode}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Terminal 1 - Start mitmweb with flow saving}:}
\li{Explain flags:}
\li{\code{\startverb --web-port\stopverb} (web UI port)}
\li{\code{\startverb --set flow_filter\stopverb} (pre-filter for Anthropic)}
\li{\code{\startverb --save-stream-file\stopverb} (continuous flow saving for programmatic access)}
\li{\strong{Verification}: Browser opens to http://127.0.0.1:8081 showing empty flow list}
\li{\strong{Note}: Flows are now also saved to \code{\startverb ~/claude-flows.mitm\stopverb} for programmatic analysis}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Terminal 2 - Start Claude Code}:}
\li{\strong{Verification}: User sees proxy configuration messages, then Claude Code starts normally}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Browser - Confirm capture}:}
\li{Have user ask Claude Code a simple question}
\li{\strong{Verification}: Request to api.anthropic.com appears in mitmweb flow list}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Verify programmatic access} (CLI + Claude Code or Both modes only):}
}

\subtree{
\title{Extract last prompt using bundled script}
\p{~/.claude/skills/cc-trace/scripts/show-last-prompt.sh}

\pre{\startverb
   - **Verification**: Script displays the user prompt that was sent to the API

**Key differences**:
- **Browser only**: Flows stored in memory only; manual review in web UI
- **CLI + Claude Code / Both**: Flows saved to disk; enables programmatic analysis with bundled scripts and custom Python scripts
- **Both mode advantage**: Combines visual exploration in browser with automated analysis capabilities

For detailed programmatic analysis methods, see [reference/usage-programmatic-access.md](reference/usage-programmatic-access.md).

\stopverb}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Teaching Traffic Inspection}
\p{Guide systematic inspection of captured requests:}

\p{\strong{Request Analysis}:}

\ol{
\li{Click on api.anthropic.com POST request in flow list}
\li{Select "Request" tab in detail panel}
\li{Point out key elements:}
\li{\strong{Headers}: \code{\startverb x-api-key\stopverb} (authentication), \code{\startverb anthropic-version\stopverb}, \code{\startverb content-type\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Body structure}: \code{\startverb model\stopverb}, \code{\startverb max_tokens\stopverb}, \code{\startverb system\stopverb}, \code{\startverb messages\stopverb}, \code{\startverb tools\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{System prompts}: Long instructional text in \code{\startverb system\stopverb} field}
\li{\strong{Tool definitions}: Array of available tools with descriptions and schemas}
\li{\strong{Context}: File contents, git status, conversation history in \code{\startverb messages\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Response Analysis}:}

\ol{
\li{Select "Response" tab}
\li{Explain streaming format (Server-Sent Events)}
\li{Point out key events:}
\li{\code{\startverb message_start\stopverb}: Metadata about response}
\li{\code{\startverb content_block_start\stopverb}: Beginning of text or tool call}
\li{\code{\startverb content_block_delta\stopverb}: Incremental content (text or tool parameters)}
\li{\code{\startverb message_delta\stopverb}: Token usage statistics}
\li{\code{\startverb message_stop\stopverb}: End of response}
}

\p{\strong{What You Can See in Captured Traffic}:}

\p{In Requests:}

\ul{
\li{System prompts and instructions given to Claude}
\li{User messages and conversation history}
\li{Tool definitions (Read, Write, Bash, Task, etc.) with descriptions and schemas}
\li{File contents loaded into context}
\li{Git status and repository information}
\li{Model configuration (temperature, max_tokens, stream settings)}
}

\p{In Responses:}

\ul{
\li{Claude's text responses and reasoning}
\li{Tool calls with complete parameters}
\li{Token usage statistics (input/output counts)}
\li{Thinking blocks (Claude's internal reasoning process)}
\li{Stop reasons (why generation ended)}
\li{Streaming events and delta updates}
}

\p{\strong{For complex streaming responses}, suggest using bundled parser:}

\pre{\startverb
# Copy raw response from mitmweb, then:
pbpaste | npx tsx ~/.claude/skills/cc-trace/scripts/parse-streamed-response.ts
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Filtering & Navigation}
\p{Teach effective filtering for focused analysis:}

\p{\strong{Common filter patterns}:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb ~d api.anthropic.com\stopverb} - Only Anthropic API}
\li{\code{\startverb ~m POST\stopverb} - Only POST requests}
\li{\code{\startverb ~u /messages\stopverb} - Only /messages endpoint}
\li{\code{\startverb ~c 200\stopverb} - Only successful responses (200 status)}
\li{\code{\startverb ~d api.anthropic.com & ~m POST\stopverb} - Combined filters (AND)}
\li{\code{\startverb ~bs 50000\stopverb} - Responses larger than 50KB}
}

\p{\strong{Keyboard shortcuts} (web interface):}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb Cmd+F\stopverb}: Search within selected flow}
\li{Click column headers to sort}
\li{Right-click → Export for saving flows}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Ending a Session}
\p{Guide users to properly close their capture session:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Exit Claude Code}: Type \code{\startverb /exit\stopverb} in Claude Code terminal, or press \code{\startverb Ctrl+C\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Stop mitmweb}: Press \code{\startverb Ctrl+C\stopverb} in the mitmweb terminal window}
\li{\strong{Clear proxy environment} (optional):}
\li{\strong{Note}: The \code{\startverb proxy_claude\stopverb} function automatically sets environment variables each time, so clearing is optional unless you want to run Claude Code without the proxy in the same terminal session}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Debugging Assistance}
\p{When troubleshooting issues, follow diagnostic procedure:}

\subtree{
\title{Issue: No Traffic Appears}
\p{\strong{Diagnostic commands}:}

\ol{
\li{Check mitmproxy is listening: \code{\startverb lsof -i :8080\stopverb}}
\li{Verify proxy environment in Claude terminal:}
\li{Test proxy with simple request: \code{\startverb curl -x http://127.0.0.1:8080 http://example.com\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Common causes}:}

\ul{
\li{mitmproxy not running}
\li{Wrong terminal used for \code{\startverb proxy_claude\stopverb} (environment variables not set)}
\li{Certificate not trusted}
\li{Port conflict (8080 or 8081 already in use)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Issue: Certificate Errors}
\p{\strong{Diagnostic}:}

\pre{\startverb
security find-certificate -c mitmproxy -a  # macOS
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Fix if missing or untrusted} (macOS):}

\pre{\startverb
# Remove old certificate
sudo security delete-certificate -c mitmproxy /Library/Keychains/System.keychain

# Re-trust certificate
sudo security add-trusted-cert -d -p ssl -p basic \
  -k /Library/Keychains/System.keychain \
  ~/.mitmproxy/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Additional steps}:}

\ul{
\li{Restart browser/Claude Code after trusting certificate}
\li{Check for multiple mitmproxy certificates (remove duplicates)}
\li{For other platforms, see [reference/setup-installation-certificate.md](reference/setup-installation-certificate.md)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Issue: Port Conflicts}
\p{\strong{Diagnostic}:}

\pre{\startverb
lsof -i :8080
lsof -i :8081
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Fix}:}

\ul{
\li{Kill conflicting process: \code{\startverb kill -9 <PID>\stopverb}}
\li{Or use alternate ports:}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Analysis Assistance}
\subtree{
\title{Learning Claude Code Internals}
\p{Guide exploration of architectural patterns:}

\p{\strong{System Prompt Analysis}:}

\ul{
\li{Compare system prompts across different tasks}
\li{Identify tool usage instructions}
\li{Note context management strategies}
\li{Understand how skills are loaded}
}

\p{\strong{Tool Call Patterns}:}

\ul{
\li{Observe when tools are called in parallel vs. sequentially}
\li{Identify tool dependencies (one result feeds into another)}
\li{Notice how TodoWrite tracks progress}
\li{Understand Task delegation to sub-agents}
}

\p{\strong{Token Usage Optimization}:}

\ul{
\li{Track input vs. output tokens across requests}
\li{Identify token-heavy operations}
\li{Observe when context is summarized}
\li{Notice when cheaper models (Haiku) are used for subtasks}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Debugging Specific Issues}
\p{\strong{For tool failures}:}

\ol{
\li{Find failed tool call in request \code{\startverb messages\stopverb} array}
\li{Examine tool parameters passed}
\li{Check response for error details}
\li{Compare with successful tool calls}
}

\p{\strong{For unexpected behavior}:}

\ol{
\li{Capture full conversation flow}
\li{Export flows for side-by-side comparison}
\li{Identify where behavior diverges}
\li{Check for context window issues (truncation)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Optimization Strategies}
\p{\strong{Teach pattern recognition}:}

\ul{
\li{When does Claude Code use parallel tool calls effectively?}
\li{How does context window management work?}
\li{When are sub-agents spawned vs. inline execution?}
\li{How are large files handled (pagination, summarization)?}
}

\p{\strong{Suggest experiments}:}

\ul{
\li{Try same task multiple times, compare token usage}
\li{Test with different model settings}
\li{Observe impact of skill loading on context}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Advanced Features}
\subtree{
\title{Python Scripting}
\p{When users want custom traffic modification, guide script creation:}

\p{\strong{Example: Request logging}}

\pre{\startverb
def request(flow):
    if "api.anthropic.com" in flow.request.pretty_url:
        print(f"→ {flow.request.method} {flow.request.path}")

def response(flow):
    if "api.anthropic.com" in flow.request.pretty_url:
        print(f"← {flow.response.status_code}")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Example: Token tracking}}

\pre{\startverb
import json

def response(flow):
    if "api.anthropic.com" in flow.request.pretty_url:
        try:
            data = json.loads(flow.response.text)
            if "usage" in data:
                usage = data["usage"]
                print(f"Tokens - Input: {usage.get('input_tokens')}, Output: {usage.get('output_tokens')}")
        except:
            pass
\stopverb}

\p{Run with: \code{\startverb mitmweb -s script.py\stopverb}}

\p{\strong{Warning}: Explain that modifying requests/responses can break functionality. Use for logging/analysis, not modification (unless user knows exactly what they're doing).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Flow Export & Replay}
\p{\strong{Exporting flows}:}

\ul{
\li{Web UI: ≡ menu → File → Export (all flows)}
\li{Right-click individual flow → Export}
\li{Formats: .mitm (native), .har (HTTP Archive)}
}

\p{\strong{Replaying flows}:}

\pre{\startverb
mitmweb -r saved-flows.mitm
\stopverb}

\p{Use for comparing past vs. current behavior}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Security & Cleanup}
\p{\strong{Emphasize security context}:}

\ul{
\li{This is for local debugging on trusted machines only}
\li{\code{\startverb NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0\stopverb} disables security - never use in production}
\li{Captured flows contain API keys and sensitive data - store securely}
\li{mitmproxy can decrypt all HTTPS traffic - only trust certificates on controlled machines}
}

\p{\strong{Cleanup after session}:}

\pre{\startverb
# Clear environment variables
unset HTTP_PROXY HTTPS_PROXY http_proxy https_proxy NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED

# Optional: Remove certificate when done with long-term analysis
sudo security delete-certificate -c mitmproxy /Library/Keychains/System.keychain

# Optional: Delete saved flows with sensitive data
find ~/claude-analysis -name "*.mitm" -delete
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Handling Different Skill Invocations}
\p{\strong{When user says}: "Help me set up cc-trace" → Start with installation verification, proceed through setup steps}

\p{\strong{When user says}: "cc-trace isn't showing traffic" → Run diagnostic procedure for traffic capture issues}

\p{\strong{When user says}: "How do I see the system prompts?" → Guide to starting capture session, then teach request inspection}

\p{\strong{When user says}: "Why is Claude Code using so many tokens?" → Guide token usage analysis workflow}

\p{\strong{When unclear}, use AskUserQuestion tool with options for: "First time setup", "Troubleshooting existing installation", "Ready to capture traffic", "Analyzing captured traffic"}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Examples}
\subtree{
\title{Example 1: Complete Setup (First-Time User)}
\p{\strong{User}: "I want to see what Claude Code is sending to the API"}

\p{\strong{Response}: "To accomplish this, set up mitmproxy to intercept Claude Code's HTTPS traffic. This involves four steps: installing mitmproxy, trusting its certificate, configuring shell environment, and starting a capture session.}

\p{First, let me check if mitmproxy is already installed. Please run this command:}

\pre{\startverb
command -v mitmproxy
\stopverb}

\p{[Uses AskUserQuestion tool to ask about command output with options: "Shows a path", "command not found", "Other"]}

\p{[User selects: "command not found"]}

\p{"Install mitmproxy using Homebrew:}

\pre{\startverb
brew install mitmproxy
\stopverb}

\p{After installation completes, verify with:}

\pre{\startverb
mitmproxy --version
\stopverb}

\p{[Uses AskUserQuestion tool to ask: "Did the installation complete successfully?" with options: "Yes, shows version X.X.X", "No, got an error", "Other"]}

\p{[User selects: "Yes, shows version 10.1.1"]}

\p{"Excellent. mitmproxy version 10.1.1 is installed. Next, generate and trust the certificate authority...}

\p{[Continue with certificate setup, then shell config, then verification]}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 2: Troubleshooting (Experienced User)}
\p{\strong{User}: "I set up mitmproxy but no traffic appears when I run Claude Code"}

\p{\strong{Response}: "To diagnose why traffic isn't appearing, check three areas: proxy status, environment configuration, and certificate trust.}

\p{First, verify mitmproxy is listening:}

\pre{\startverb
lsof -i :8080
\stopverb}

\p{[Uses AskUserQuestion tool: "What does the lsof command show?" with options: "Shows mitmproxy process listening", "No output / port not in use", "Shows different process", "Other"]}

\p{[User selects: "Shows mitmproxy process listening"]}

\p{"Good - mitmproxy is running. Next, check proxy environment in the terminal where Claude Code is running:}

\pre{\startverb
echo $HTTP_PROXY
echo $NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS
\stopverb}

\p{[Uses AskUserQuestion tool: "What values do the environment variables show?" with options: "Both show correct values (proxy URL and cert path)", "One or both are empty", "Shows unexpected values", "Other"]}

\p{[Diagnose based on response, guide to fix]}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 3: Analysis Guidance (Active User)}
\p{\strong{User}: "I'm looking at a request but there's so much JSON. Where are the system prompts?"}

\p{\strong{Response}: "To locate system prompts in captured requests, examine the request body structure:}

\ol{
\li{In mitmweb, click the api.anthropic.com POST request}
\li{Select the 'Request' tab}
\li{Look for the \code{\startverb system\stopverb} field in the JSON body}
}

\p{The \code{\startverb system\stopverb} field contains a long text string with instructions to Claude. For example:}

\pre{\startverb
{
  "model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929",
  "system": "You are Claude Code, Anthropic's official CLI for Claude...",
  "messages": [...],
  "tools": [...]
}
\stopverb}

\p{The \code{\startverb system\stopverb} value is the complete system prompt. To read it more easily:}

\ol{
\li{Click within the system prompt text}
\li{Use Cmd+F to search for specific keywords}
\li{Or copy the entire request body and format it with \code{\startverb jq\stopverb}:}
}

\pre{\startverb
pbpaste | jq .system
\stopverb}

\p{[Uses AskUserQuestion tool: "What specific aspect of the system prompt are you interested in?" with options: "Tool usage instructions", "Context management strategies", "How skills are loaded", "General understanding of how Claude Code works", multiSelect: true]}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Conversation Context}
